.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhcltech-cisco-partner-to-launch-ai-powered-meeting-rooms-services-123110700791_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Meeting-Rooms-as-a-Service%20(MRaaS)%20will%20enable%20users%20to%20join%20meetings%20from%20any%20meeting%20solution%20provider%20using%20Cisco's%20Webex%20devices%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhcltech-cisco-partner-to-launch-ai-powered-meeting-rooms-services-123110700791_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhcltech-cisco-partner-to-launch-ai-powered-meeting-rooms-services-123110700791_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhcltech-cisco-partner-to-launch-ai-powered-meeting-rooms-services-123110700791_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Two%20IAS%20Officers%20Chaperoned%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Bill%20Despite%20RBI's%20Objections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07155525%2FUntitled-design-5.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20finished%20hearing%20arguments%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20will%20hopefully%20deliver%20a%20judgment%20soon.%20I%20say%20hopefully%20because%20it%20has%20now%20been%20six%20years%20since%20the%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%202017%20Budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20readers%20will%20not%20know%20the%20background%20to%20the%20bonds%20and%20what%20they%20are.%20In%20brief%2C%20it%20allows%20unlimited%2C%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20any%20registered%20political%20party.%20The%20scheme%20also%20allows%20anyone%2C%20including%20foreign%20governments%2C%20criminal%20gangs%20and%20of%20course%20corporate%20interests%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20influence%20political%20parties%20because%20parties%20could%20accept%20money%20without%20revealing%20who%20gave%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20to%20fund%20a%20party%20anonymously%20was%20made%20easy.%20Bonds%20would%20be%20available%20in%20denominations%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20at%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20branches%20in%2029%20cities.%20A%20donor%20could%20purchase%20them%20through%20their%20bank%20account%20and%20hand%20them%20over%20to%20the%20party%20or%20individual%20of%20their%20choice%2C%20who%20could%20encash%20them.%20They%20would%20be%20valid%20for%2015%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20should%20alert%20us%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20something%20was%20off%20from%20the%20start.%20Four%20days%20before%20Budget%202017%2C%20a%20bureaucrat%20spotted%20the%20scheme%20in%20then%20finance%20minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%E2%80%99s%20speech%2C%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20assent%20was%20required.%20This%20was%20because%20the%20introduction%20of%20bonds%20required%20changes%20to%20the%20RBI%20Act%2C%20something%20that%20the%20government%20apparently%20did%20not%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-questions-anonymity-of-electoral-bonds-and-voters-right-to-information%5C%22%3ESC%20Questions%20Anonymity%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20and%20Voters%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20drafted%20a%20proposed%20amendment%20to%20align%20the%20law%20with%20the%20change%20and%20sent%20the%20file%20up%20the%20ranks%20for%20the%20finance%20minister%20to%20see.%20The%20same%20day%2C%20January%2028%2C%202017%2C%20a%20Saturday%2C%20the%20RBI%20was%20sent%20a%20five-line%20email%20seeking%20its%20comments.%20The%20reply%20came%20on%20Monday%2C%20January%2030.%20The%20RBI%20said%20it%20was%20a%20bad%20idea%20as%20it%20went%20against%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20authority%20as%20the%20sole%20issuer%20of%20bearer%20instruments%2C%20meaning%20cash.%20These%20bonds%2C%20as%20they%20were%20anonymous%2C%20could%20become%20currency%20and%20undermine%20the%20faith%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20point%2C%20the%20RBI%20was%20unambiguous%3A%20amending%20the%20law%20to%20facilitate%20this%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20seriously%20undermine%20a%20core%20principle%20of%20central%20banking%20legislation%20and%20doing%20so%20would%20set%20a%20bad%20precedent%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20objection%20the%20RBI%20had%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceven%20the%20intended%20purpose%20of%20the%20transparency%20might%20not%20be%20achievable%20as%20the%20original%20buyer%20of%20the%20instrument%20(bond)%20need%20not%20be%20the%20actual%20contributor%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%9D.%20If%20person%20A%20purchased%20the%20bond%20and%20then%20sold%20it%2C%20at%20face%20value%20or%20more%2C%20to%20any%20entity%2C%20including%20a%20foreign%20government%2C%20that%20entity%20could%20gift%20it%20to%20a%20party.%20The%20nameless%20bond%20was%20as%20good%20as%20cash.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20bonds%20are%20bearer%20bonds%20and%20transferable%20by%20delivery%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20RBI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Chence%2C%20who%20finally%20and%20actually%20contributes%20the%20bond%20to%20the%20political%20party%20will%20not%20be%20known%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20point%20it%20made%20was%20that%20what%20was%20proposed%20through%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20%E2%80%94%20transfer%20of%20money%20from%20bank%20accounts%20of%20entities%20to%20political%20parties%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20done%20through%20a%20cheque%2C%20bank%20transfer%20or%20demand%20draft.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20special%20need%20for%2C%20or%20advantage%20by%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20Electoral%20Bearer%20Bond%2C%20that%20too%20by%20disturbing%20an%20established%20international%20practice.%E2%80%9D%20The%20man%20charged%20with%20steering%20the%20thing%20through%20was%20Hasmukh%20Adhia%2C%20an%20IAS%20officer%20from%20Gujarat%20with%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20yoga.%20(He%20had%20earlier%20chaperoned%20the%20GST%20Bill%2C%20and%20after%20he%20retired%2C%20was%20made%20chairman%20of%20the%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20and%20chancellor%20of%20the%20Central%20University%20of%20Gujarat).%20He%20dismissed%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20objections%20on%20two%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-fatf-report-bjp-constitution%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20Contrary%20to%20PMLA%2C%20Favours%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99%3A%20Coalition%20Report%20Tells%20FATF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20appears%20the%20RBI%20has%20not%20understood%20the%20proposed%20mechanism%20of%20having%20pre-paid%20instruments%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20keeping%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20donor%20secret%2C%20while%20ensuring%20the%20donation%20is%20made%20only%20out%20of%20fully%20tax-paid%20money%20of%20a%20person.%E2%80%9D%20By%20this%20he%20meant%20because%20the%20original%20purchaser%20had%20to%20acquire%20the%20bonds%20through%20their%20official%20account%2C%20it%20made%20the%20donation%20clean.%20This%20was%20not%20a%20response%20to%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20specific%20objections.%20Adhia%20said%20the%2015-day%20time%20limit%20for%20redemption%20would%20mitigate%20against%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20other%20fears%2C%20without%20explaining%20how.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CAlso%20this%20advice%20has%20come%20quite%20late%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Finance%20Bill%20is%20already%20printed.%E2%80%9D%20It%20had%20actually%20come%20within%20hours%20of%20being%20sent%20for.%20It%20was%20hardly%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20fault%20that%20the%20advice%20had%20not%20been%20sought%20earlier.%20This%20was%20deceit%2C%20but%20Adhia%20concluded%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20may%2C%20therefore%2C%20go%20ahead%20with%20our%20proposal%E2%80%9D.%20His%20colleague%2C%20economic%20affairs%20secretary%20Tapan%20Ray%2C%20concurred%20with%20Adhia%20the%20same%20day%2C%20and%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20February%201%2C%20Jaitley%20announced%20the%20scheme%20which%20became%20law%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Union%20Budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20journalist%20Nitin%20Sethi%20of%20Huffington%20Post%20(which%20carried%20a%20six-part%20investigation%20into%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20based%20on%20documents%20procured%20by%20RTI%20activist%20Commodore%20Lokesh%20Batra)%20why%20the%20government%20had%20ignored%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20objections%2C%20the%20finance%20ministry%20said%20it%20had%20taken%20the%20decision%20%E2%80%9Cin%20good%20faith%20and%20in%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20law%20was%20passed%2C%20the%20details%20were%20not%20made%20public.%20This%20came%20in%20June%202017%2C%20when%20Tapan%20Ray%20revealed%20how%20the%20bonds%20would%20work%20in%20practice%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20information%20regarding%20purchaser%20and%20payee%20shall%20be%20kept%20secret%20by%20the%20issuer%20bank.%20These%20details%20would%20be%20beyond%20the%20purview%20of%20RTI.%E2%80%9D%20(Ray%20was%20made%20chairman%20of%20the%20Central%20Bank%20of%20India%20after%20he%20retired%20in%202018%2C%20and%20in%202019%20was%20also%20made%20CEO%20and%20managing%20director%20of%20Gujarat%20International%20Finance%20Tec%20City.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20body%20to%20say%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20dangerous%20was%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20In%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20it%20said%20that%20to%20exclude%20the%20reporting%20of%20donations%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20would%20have%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20repercussions%20on%20the%20transparency%20aspect%20of%20political%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20for%20six%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20politics%20has%20been%20funded%20anonymously.%20It%20is%20time%20to%20end%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699354833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07155525%2FUntitled-design-5.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-two-ias-officers-chaperoned-the-electoral-bonds-bill-despite-rbis-objections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20objections%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20too%2C%20for%20six%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20politics%20has%20been%20funded%20anonymously.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-two-ias-officers-chaperoned-the-electoral-bonds-bill-despite-rbis-objections%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Usha%20Uthup%20on%20learning%20about%20food%20through%20music%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699354662000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105039697%2Cimgsize-13864.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fusha-uthup-i-was-unaware-of-what-paneer-was-until-my-singing-career-exposed-me-to-these-culinary-delightsexclusive%2Farticleshow%2F105039420.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105039420.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUsha%20Uthup%2C%20the%20popular%20singer%20and%20actor%2C%20spoke%20about%20the%20simplicity%20of%20life%20in%20her%20childhood%20and%20how%20today's%20generation%20craves%20more.%20She%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20maintaining%20focus%20and%20commitment%20to%20achieve%20success%2C%20despite%20the%20distractions%20and%20desires%20that%20come%20with%20exposure%20to%20various%20things.%20Usha%20reminisced%20about%20her%20childhood%2C%20where%20simple%20pleasures%20like%20street%20food%20brought%20contentment.%20She%20mentioned%2