ption%3EReturn-to-office%20mandates%20indicate%20a%20failure%20of%20imagination%20on%20the%20part%20of%20management%20and%20a%20refusal%20to%20do%20the%20work%20necessary%20to%20create%20a%20positive%20company%20culture.%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-empire-of-surveillance-leveraging-monopoly-power-tracking-purchases-2022-8%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20its%20%241.3%20trillion%20empire%20largely%20by%20tracking%20and%20evaluating%3C%2Fa%3E%20almost%20every%20aspect%20of%20a%20customer's%20life.%20From%20a%20new%20TV%20to%20a%20toilet-paper%20refill%2C%20Amazon%20knows%20what%20a%20customer%20wants%20and%20when%20they%20want%20it%2C%20and%20it's%20always%20ready%20to%20serve%20it%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-phrase-shows-amazons-data-obsession-2015-10%5C%22%3Eobsession%20with%20metrics%20and%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20extend%20to%20certain%20parts%20of%20Amazon's%20workplace.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20the%20company%20has%20aggressively%20pushed%20employees%20back%20to%20the%20office.%20In%20February%2C%20Amazon%20announced%20that%20employees%20would%20be%20required%20to%20come%20into%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%20and%20since%20then%2C%20the%20e-commerce%20giant%20has%20escalated%20its%20battle%20with%20remote%20employees%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-outraged-new-email-warning-about-individual-office-attendance-2023-8%5C%22%3Esending%20emails%20to%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20their%20attendance%2C%20creating%20internal%20dashboards%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-forced-rto-tracking-employee-office-attendance-2023-9%5C%22%3Edisplay%20how%20many%20days%20a%20week%20each%20employee%20was%20coming%20into%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20telling%20managers%20in%20October%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-lets-managers-terminate-employees-return-to-office-2023-10%5C%22%3Ethey%20could%20begin%20firing%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20weren't%20meeting%20the%20return-to-office%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-return-to-office-policy-petition-30000-staff-remote-work-2023-3%5C%22%3Eperturbed%20employees%20have%20pressed%20executives%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20mandate%2C%20supposedly%20data-obsessed%20higher-ups%20have%20seemed%20to%20have%20no%20data%20to%20justify%20it.%20Asked%20in%20August%20about%20this%2C%20Mike%20Hopkins%2C%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20Prime%20Video%20and%20Amazon%20Studios%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-executive-no-data-to-support-return-to-office-mandate-2023-8%5C%22%3Eoffered%20a%20vague%20response%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bno%20data%20either%20way%26quot%3B%20on%20whether%20mandating%20in-office%20work%20made%20people%20more%20productive%20but%20that%20executives%20believe%20Amazon's%20workers%20do%20their%20best%20work%20when%20they're%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20reasonable%20to%20wonder%20why%20Amazon%2C%20a%20company%20that%20has%20data%20on%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20and%20their%20decisions%2C%20is%20struggling%20to%20come%20up%20with%20hard%20numbers%20to%20back%20up%20its%20dictatorial%20push%20back%20to%20the%20office.%20Perhaps%20the%20reason%20is%20that%20the%20data%20supporting%20Amazon%20and%20other%20companies'%20RTO%20policies%20is%20threadbare%2C%20relying%20mostly%20on%20a%20few%20studies%20that%20use%20sample%20sets%20of%20questionable%20usefulness%20to%20back%20up%20their%20claims%20that%20remote%20work%20is%20less%20productive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20weakness%20of%20the%20evidence%20won't%20stop%20bosses%20from%20making%20these%20RTO%20mandates.%20They%20indicate%20a%20failure%20of%20imagination%20on%20the%20part%20of%20management%20and%20a%20refusal%20to%20do%20the%20work%20necessary%20to%20create%20a%20positive%20company%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEvidence%20is%20as%20evidence%20does%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20return-to-office%20battle%20has%20heated%20up%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20marked%20increase%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-back-to-the-office-what-the-data-really-says-2023-9%5C%22%3Edeclarations%20that%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-remote-jobs-more-productive-work-life-balance-return-office-2023-8%5C%22%3Eless%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20diving%20deeper%20into%20this%20evidence%20reveals%20flawed%20logic%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20media%20industry%20obsessed%20with%20proving%20bosses%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20that%20has%20most%20often%20been%20used%20to%20argue%20for%20the%20necessity%20of%20in-office%20work%20is%20a%20July%20working%20paper%20from%20researchers%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw31515%2Fw31515.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20randomly%20assigned%20data-entry%20workers%20at%20a%20company%20in%20India%20to%20work%20either%20from%20home%20or%20in%20the%20office%20for%20eight%20weeks.%20The%20researchers%20determined%20that%20remote%20workers%20were%2018%25%20less%20productive%20than%20their%20in-person%20counterparts.%20Journalists%20have%20consistently%20cited%20this%20study%20without%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20taking%20a%20moment%20to%20consider%20its%20findings.%20First%20and%20foremost%2C%20it's%20farcical%20to%20use%20the%20work%20of%20entry-level%20data%20workers%20in%20India%20%E2%80%94%20who%20were%20%3Cem%3Erecruited%20specifically%20for%20the%20study%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20all%20employees%20in%20all%20industries%20around%20the%20world.%20Secondly%2C%20the%20measurement%20of%20their%20productivity%20was%20%26quot%3Bnet%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20number%20of%20correct%20entries%20they%20made%20in%20a%20minute.%20The%20%26quot%3Bdrop%20in%20productivity%26quot%3B%20is%20really%20about%20how%20fast%20people%20could%20put%20numbers%20into%20a%20sheet%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20not%20what%20most%20people%20do%20at%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Ffinance-and-economics%2F2023%2F06%2F28%2Fthe-working-from-home-delusion-fades%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutlets%20cited%20a%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20examined%20the%20productivity%20of%2010%2C000%20workers%20at%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbfi.uchicago.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2FBFI_WP_2021-56.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAsian%20IT-services%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20central%20claim%20seems%20to%20be%20tailor-made%20for%20RTO%20advocates%3A%20The%20researchers%20estimated%20a%20productivity%20shortfall%20of%208%25%20to%2019%25%20when%20workers%20transitioned%20from%20working%20at%20the%20office%20to%20working%20from%20home.%20The%20study's%20authors%20found%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Bslight%20decline%20in%20output%26quot%3B%20but%20acknowledged%20workers%20were%20stretching%20out%20their%20working%20hours%20at%20home%3B%20those%20things%20together%20showed%20up%20as%20a%20drop%20in%20productivity.%20Here%20too%2C%20there%20are%20issues.%20%26quot%3BOutput%26quot%3B%20in%20this%20case%20refers%20to%20%26quot%3Bperformance%20against%20the%20semi-annual%20goal%20on%20a%20key%20performance%20metric%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20lines%20of%20useful%20code%20written%20by%20a%20developer.%20The%20authors%20described%20these%20metrics%20as%20%26quot%3Bobjective%26quot%3B%20and%20tracked%2C%20but%20the%20actual%20composition%20of%20these%20metrics%20is%20still%20pretty%20vague%20and%20based%20on%20managers'%20interpretations%20of%20their%20value.%20Additionally%2C%20hours%20worked%20were%20logged%20by%20an%20employee-surveillance%20software%20%E2%80%94%20but%20these%20sorts%20of%20tools%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2022%2F06%2Fmonitoring-employees-makes-them-more-likely-to-break-rules%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecome%20with%20plenty%20of%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20should%20make%20anyone%20skeptical%20of%20their%20efficacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThese%20studies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20RTO%20push%20%E2%80%94%20often%20betray%20an%20utter%20ignorance%20of%20the%20workplace%20and%20work%20itself%2C%20both%20its%20structure%20and%20its%20outputs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20notice%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20studies%20focus%20on%20call%20centers%20(the%20Stanford%20researcher%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1kqbngD8pemqxAkZmWCOQ32Yk6PXK9eVA%2Fview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENicholas%20Bloom%20cited%20two%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20his%20roundup%20of%20productivity%20research)%2C%20and%20that's%20likely%20because%20these%20are%20extremely%20controlled%20and%20heavily%20micromanaged%20environments%20%E2%80%94%20ones%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2022%2F11%2F01%2F1132931674%2Fmedicaid-and-medicare-hotline-workers-strike-over-pay-and-working-conditions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erife%20with%20labor%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Crude%20measures%20of%20productivity%20might%20indeed%20slip%20when%20workers%20are%20able%20to%20get%20away%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.askamanager.org%2F2010%2F05%2Fcall-center-job-misery.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehorrible%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fnot-allowed-to-hang-up-the-harsh-reality-of-working-in-customer-service%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20torrents%20of%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bproductivity%26quot%3B%20in%20these%20studies%20is%20always%20a%20rigid%20metric%2C%20like%20%26quot%3Bcalls%20answered%2C%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20something%20more%20meaningful%2C%20like%20whether%20a%20problem%20was%20fixed%20or%20whether%20the%20customer%20was%20happy.%20These%20studies%20are%20relatively%20useless%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20evaluating%20most%20companies'%20return-to-office%20strategies%2C%20but%20that's%20just%20fine%20for%20the%20managerial%20elite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20somebody%20who's%20been%20writing%20about%20this%20subject%20for%20years%20(and%20who's%20worked%20remotely%20since%202012)%2C%20I've%20yet%20to%20read%20a%20single%20piece%20of%20research%20that%20convincingly%20backs%20up%20the%20assertion%20that%20we%20%3Cem%3Eneed%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office.%20And%20yet%20major%20media%20outlets%20have%20continued%20to%20feed%20bosses'%20narrative%20that%20we%20%26quot%3Bdo%20better%20work%20together.%26quot%3B%20The%20existing%20studies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-work-from-home-employees-better-boss-managers-ceo-2022-6%5C%22%3Econtinually%20fail%20to%20evaluate%20real%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%20they%20prioritize%20speed%2C%20betraying%20the%20same%20corporate%20ignorance%20forcing%20people%20back%20to%20the%20office.%20These%20studies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20RTO%20push%20%E2%80%94%20often%20betray%20an%20utter%20ignorance%20of%20the%20workplace%20and%20work%20itself%2C%20both%20its%20structure%20and%20its%20outputs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJust%20the%20vibes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20limited%20evidence%20against%20it%2C%20corporations%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-from-home-return-to-office-americans-employment-wfh-2023-10%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20trying%20to%20kill%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Corporate%20statements%20about%20these%20decisions%20never%20seem%20to%20justify%20the%20shift%20beyond%20platitudes%20about%20%26quot%3Btogetherness%26quot%3B%20and%20vague%20references%20to%20%26quot%3Bculture.%26quot%3B%20Look%20deeper%2C%20though%2C%20and%20they%20reveal%20the%20rotten%20core%20of%20the%20mandates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoblox%2C%20a%20company%20that%20derives%20its%20revenue%20from%20digital%20worlds%2C%20reversed%20its%20flexible%20work%20policy%20in%20October%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Froblox-staff-return-office-three-days-week-resign-severance-rto-2023-10%5C%22%3Etelling%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20if%20they%20didn't%20work%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%20in%20the%20office%20they'd%20be%20laid%20off.%20The%20reason%20for%20the%20about-face%3F%20Based%20on%20its%20CEO%20David%20Baszucki's%20blog%20post%20announcing%20the%20move%2C%20it%20seems%20mostly%20about%20vibes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20personally%20hoped%20that%20for%20our%20culture%20and%20our%20type%20of%20work%2C%20it%20might%20be%20possible%20to%20imagine%20a%20heavily%20hybrid%20remote%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20was%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20for%20me%20when%20we%20had%20our%20first%20post-quarantine%2C%20in-person%20group%20gathering.%20Within%2045%20minutes%20I%20came%20away%20from%20three%20separate%20conversations%20with%20spontaneous%20to%20do's%20and%20ideas%20to%20put%20in%20motion%2C%20something%20that%20hadn't%20happened%20during%20the%20past%20few%20years%20of%20video%20meetings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENike's%20four-days-a-week%20policy%20points%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oregonlive.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2Fnike-says-employees-must-return-to-the-office-four-days-each-week.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20power%20and%20energy%20that%20comes%20from%20working%20together%20in%20person%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Geico%20said%20its%20return-to-office%20program%20was%20meant%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wptv.com%2Fgeico-confirms-significant-layoffs-pushes-for-return-to-office%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efoster%20a%20sense%20of%20community%20and%20connection%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20but%20offered%20little%20data%20to%20support%20the%20decision.%20The%20only%20numbers%20in%20the%20announcement%20appeared%20to%20be%20about%20layoffs%3A%20Geico%20said%20it%20was%20letting%202%2C000%20people%20go%20to%20sustain%20%26quot%3Blong-term%20profitability%20and%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20suggesting%20that%20while%20layoffs%20can%20be%20evaluated%20with%20data%2C%20in-person%20work%20can%20only%20be%20backed%20up%20with%20mood%20rings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EManagers%20and%20executives%20make%20calls%20based%20on%20perception%20rather%20than%20hands-on%20experience%20or%20data.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20announcements%20are%20almost%20always%20issued%20by%20executives%20who%20probably%20won't%20be%20subjected%20to%20the%20same%20kinds%20of%20check-ins%20as%20the%20rank-and-file%20workers%20the%20mandates%20apply%20to.%20Nobody's%20asking%20Amazon's%20Andy%20Jassy%20or%20Geico's%20Todd%20Combs%20how%20many%20days%20they%20swiped%20into%20the%20office%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20chance%20Oracle%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaked-email-shows-oracle-forcing-employees-return-to-office-2023-3%5C%22%3Ewhich%20instituted%20a%20return-to-office%20policy%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20would%20punish%20Safra%20Catz%20or%20Larry%20Ellison%20for%20spending%20too%20little%20time%20at%20their%20desk.%20This%20irony%20combined%20with%20vague%20justifications%20exposes%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20RTO%20push%3A%20Managers%20and%20executives%20make%20calls%20based%20on%20perception%20rather%20than%20hands-on%20experience%20or%20data.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-replace-ai-job-employees-executives-save-money-salary-2023-9%5C%22%3EThe%20modern%20CEO%20has%20become%20a%20figurehead%3C%2Fa%3E%20reaping%20the%20rewards%20of%20a%20work%20process%20they%20don't%20meaningfully%20participate%20in%2C%20so%20they%20make%20their%20choices%20based%20on%20macroeconomic%20conditions%2C%20their%20own%20biases%2C%20or%2C%20evidently%2C%20a%20single%2045-minute%20meeting%20that%20left%20them%20feeling%20good.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowhere%20is%20this%20more%20obvious%20than%20at%20Meta%2C%20where%20workers%20are%20required%20to%20return%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20The%20only%20problem%3A%20Employees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-rto-mess-return-to-office-remote-work-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecan't%20find%20the%20space%20or%20the%20privacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20actually%20do%20their%20work%20at%20the%20office%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20issue%20is%20almost%20too%20on%20the%20nose.%20The%20honchos%20calling%20the%20shots%20at%20Meta%2C%20a%20company%20that%20has%20caused%20global%20discord%20through%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcambridge-analytica-a-guide-to-the-trump-linked-data-firm-that-harvested-50-million-facebook-profiles-2018-3%5C%22%3Ehandling%20of%20people's%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20appear%20to%20be%20unaware%20of%20how%20people%20at%20the%20company%20do%20their%20jobs.%20More%20frustratingly%2C%20Meta's%20corporate%20guidelines%20say%20that%20anyone%20who%20has%20worked%20at%20the%20company%20for%2018%20months%20or%20more%20can%20apply%20to%20become%20a%20permanent%20remote%20worker%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nice%20idea%2C%20except%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-rto-mess-return-to-office-remote-work-2023-9%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20people%20have%20applied%20and%20have%20yet%20to%20hear%20back%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBecause%20I%20said%20so%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20and%20sustaining%20a%20positive%2C%20productive%20corporate%20culture%20takes%20work.%20It%20requires%20managers%20and%20executives%20who%20truly%20understand%20the%20product%20their%20employees%20are%20putting%20out%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20is%20required%20to%20create%20that%20product.%20That's%20what%20makes%20the%20move%20to%20kill%20off%20remote%20work%20so%20frustrating.%20It's%20not%20clear%20that%20the%20return-to-office%20move%20is%20about%20making%20workers%20more%20productive%20or%20building%20a%20better%20culture.%20Rather%2C%20it's%20becoming%20obvious%20that%20these%20mandates%20are%20mostly%20an%20attempt%20to%20reestablish%20a%20surveillance%20society%20that%20allows%20managers%20to%20skip%20over%20the%20tough%20task%20of%20building%20a%20company%20where%20people%20actually%20want%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20RTO%20push%20is%20eyewash%20for%20investors%20to%20prove%20that%20drops%20in%20revenue%20and%20profitability%20aren't%20a%20result%20of%20poor%20managerial%20decisions%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feric-adams-work-from-home-pajamas-quote-nyc-mayor-office-2022-2%5C%22%3Ethe%20result%20of%20lazy%20workers%20sitting%20at%20home%20in%20their%20pajamas%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20it's%20a%20genius%20move%20for%20executives%20%E2%80%94%20a%20way%20to%20establish%20control%20over%20workers%20during%20an%20unprecedented%20societal%20awareness%20of%20labor%20rights%20(thanks%20to%20the%20striking%20workers%20of%20the%20Writers%20Guild%20of%20America%2C%20SAG-AFTRA%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Auto%20Workers)%20while%20also%20shifting%20the%20blame%20and%20consequences%20of%20poor%20stock%20performance%20onto%20those%20least%20responsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EReal%20management%20takes%20responsibility%20and%20makes%20thoughtful%20decisions%20based%20on%20what%20makes%20a%20company%20stronger.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20perhaps%20have%20more%20sympathy%20if%20companies%20made%20even%20the%20lightest%20attempt%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20efficacy%20of%20office%20work%20through%20relevant%20data%20or%20definable%20productivity%20metrics%2C%20rather%20than%20vague%20references%20to%20hours%20worked%20or%20office%20attendance.%20But%20seeing%20this%20type%20of%20data%20is%20unlikely%20as%20corporations%20have%20mostly%20turned%20modern%20managers%20into%20hall%20monitors.%20And%20if%2C%20as%20some%20have%20suggested%2C%20the%20return-to-office%20push%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F09%2F12%2Fwhy-rto-mandates-are-layoffs-in-disguise-according-to-workplace-experts.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20attempt%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20layoff%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20instituting%20unreasonable%20policies%20to%20make%20people%20quit%20(or%20accept%20severance)%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20corporate%20cowardice.%20It's%20restructuring%20a%20company%20based%20on%20who's%20most%20willing%20to%20tolerate%20wrongheaded%20inconveniences%2C%20rejecting%20great%20workers%20who%20don't%20live%20close%20to%20an%20office%2C%20and%20galvanizing%20sycophants%20who%20are%20willing%20to%20uncritically%20cheer%20on%20every%20executive%20mandate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20executives%20may%20see%20a%20return-to-office%20push%20as%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20I%20believe%20these%20mandates%20will%20only%20weaken%20their%20organizations%2C%20driving%20a%20wedge%20between%20management%20and%20workers.%20Forcing%20in-person%20attendance%20without%20clear%20goals%20and%20reasoning%20is%20going%20to%20create%20an%20outright%20hostility%20toward%20higher-ups.%20This%20pointless%20and%20petty%20crusade%20does%20nothing%20to%20make%20organizations%20better%2C%20leaner%2C%20or%20more%20productive%20%E2%80%94%20all%20it%20does%20is%20temporarily%20help%20executives%20distract%20from%20larger%20organizational%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20management%20takes%20responsibility%20and%20makes%20thoughtful%20decisions%20based%20on%20what%20makes%20a%20company%20stronger.%20The%20return-to-office%20move%20is%20the%20exact%20opposite%3A%20an%20unproductive%20push%20for%20control%20that%20erodes%20the%20already%20tenuous%20loyalty%20workers%20have%20to%20their%20employers%20while%20failing%20to%20address%20core%20problems%20of%20managerial%20competency%20that%20will%20only%20get%20worse%20as%20decent%20employees%20flee%20these%20dimwitted%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fed-zitron%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%2230622930977e2f284bf31e6ed102090a%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fed-zitron%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EEd%20Zitron%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20CEO%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ezpr.com%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22b1c98f0cdec5c63f2b2f21fa6d1930d6%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ezpr.com%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEZPR%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20national%20tech%20and%20business%20public-relations%20agency.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20the%20tech%20and%20culture%20newsletter%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fez.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22bf06b652261f32a36c039bec2337ce77%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fez.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%