p%3EI%20tried%20to%20load%20up%20the%20biscuit%20sandwich%20with%20extra%20meats%2C%20hoping%20for%20a%20good%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ordered%20it%20with%20bacon%20and%20sausage.%20That%20strategy%20didn't%20work.%20The%20McDonald's%20biscuit%20was%20visually%20appealing.%20But%20that's%20it.%20It%20was%20greasy%20and%20spongy.%20The%20components%20needed%20a%20sauce%20to%20bring%20all%20the%20flavors%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biscuit%20sandwich%20didn't%20come%20close%20to%20being%20as%20tasty%20and%20easy%20to%20eat%20as%20the%20Crunchwrap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETaco%20Bell%20recently%20added%20a%20breakfast%20taco%20to%20the%20menu.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Review%20of%20Taco%20Bell's%20breakfast%20taco.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6549086936d588dc55cb6438%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20new%20Taco%20Bell%20breakfast%20taco%20was%20bland.%3Cp%3ENancy%20Luna%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaco-bell-tests-chicken-nuggets-competitor-mcdonalds-mcnuggets-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaco%20Bell%3C%2Fa%3E%20introduced%20a%20toasted%20breakfast%20taco.%20I%20know%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20believe%20it%20didn't%20have%20one%20before.%20I%20have%20tried%20the%20new%20breakfast%20taco%20twice.%20Once%20was%20at%20the%20Taco%20Bell%20headquarters%20for%20a%20media%20preview.%20The%20second%20time%20was%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20reaction%20was%20the%20same%20for%20both%20tastings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20taco%20is%20not%20a%20demonstration%20of%20Taco%20Bell%20stepping%20up%20its%20breakfast%20game.%20The%20toasted%20tortilla%20adds%20texture%20to%20an%20otherwise%20bland%20taco%20stuffed%20with%20crumbled%20sausage%2C%20scrambled%20eggs%2C%20and%20melted%20shredded%20cheese.%20I%20suggest%20ordering%20it%20with%20Taco%20Bell's%20delicious%20Chipotle%20sauce%20to%20give%20it%20a%20flavor%20kick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHopefully%2C%20Taco%20Bell%20will%20have%20something%20better%20up%20its%20sleeve%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20breakfast%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMcDonald's%20is%20resting%20on%20its%20laurels.%20It%20loses%20this%20breakfast%20battle%20to%20Taco%20Bell.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221810%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Taco%20Bell%20breakfast%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65490b3bb788914e5550e032%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221099%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETaco%20Bell's%20breakfast%20beats%20the%20menu%20at%20McDonald's.%3Cp%3ETaco%20Bell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20all%20the%20classics%20at%20McDonald's%20and%20couldn't%20find%20one%20addictive%20breakfast%20sandwich%20or%20burrito.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20nearly%20got%20ill%20looking%20at%20their%20version%20of%20a%20breakfast%20burrito.%20The%20chain%20is%20not%20innovating%20at%20breakfast.%20The%20only%20major%20breakfast%20promotion%20McDonald's%20has%20done%20this%20year%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-krispy-kreme-doughnuts-kentucky-more-expensive-not-as-fresh-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etesting%20the%20sale%20of%20Krispy%20Kreme%20doughnuts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hawking%20another%20brand's%20product%20is%20not%20creative.%20That's%20lazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaco%20Bell%20is%20not%20perfect.%20But%20it%20wins%20this%20battle%20because%20the%20Breakfast%20Crunchwrap%20is%20supreme.%20It%20is%20a%20fast-food%20star%20at%20breakfast%2C%20beating%20any%20morning%20grub%20McDonald's%20has%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20fast-food%20insider%20or%20worker%20with%20insight%20to%20share%3F%20Got%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Anluna%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Enluna%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20via%20Signal%20encrypted%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22tel%3A7148756218%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E714-875-6218%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaco-bell-vs-mcdonalds-which-has-better-breakfast-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699352702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65490531b788914e5550d9e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaco-bell-vs-mcdonalds-which-has-better-breakfast-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Who%20wins%20in%20the%20Taco%20Bell%20vs.%20McDonalds%20debate%3F%20Taco%20Bell%20aims%20to%20outshine%20McDonald's%20in%20serving%20crave-worthy%20morning%20meals.%20We%20reviewed%20both%20to%20see%20which%20is%20best.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nluna%40insider.com%20(Nancy%20Luna)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaco-bell-vs-mcdonalds-which-has-better-breakfast-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20former%20Google%20recruiter.%20The%20smartest%20job%20candidates%20always%20did%20these%205%20things%20to%20stand%20out.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nolan%20Church%20a%20former%20Google%20recruiter%20shares%20how%20interviewees%20can%20stand%20out.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536991b0487ff031cabc4d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENolan%20Church%2C%20a%20former%20Google%20recruiter%2C%20says%20interviewees%20should%20look%20for%20ways%20to%20stand%20out.%3Cp%3ENolan%20Church%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EA%20former%20recruiter%20for%20Google%2C%20Nolan%20Church%20now%20runs%20Continuum%2C%20a%20talent%20marketplace%20for%20executives.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20the%20best%20job%20applicants%20are%20prepared%20with%20anecdotes%20that%20illustrate%20lessons%20they've%20learned.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ELook%20for%20ways%20to%20establish%20friendly%20connections%20with%20employees%20before%20you%20even%20apply%2C%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Nolan%20Church%2C%20a%2034-year-old%20former%20recruiter%20for%20Google%20and%20Doordash%20from%20Salt%20Lake%20City%2C%20Utah.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20opening%20Continuum%2C%20a%20talent%20marketplace%20for%20executives%2C%20I%20worked%20as%20a%20recruiter%20for%20Google.%20I%20also%20led%20the%20recruiting%20team%20at%20DoorDash%20where%20I%20saw%20the%20company%20grow%20from%2050%20to%20800%20employees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20hiring%2C%20I%20tell%20job%20seekers%20that%20when%20you%20apply%20online%2C%20you%20should%20never%20expect%20to%20hear%20back%20from%20that%20company.%20The%20reason%3A%20There%20are%20way%20too%20many%20people%20applying%20for%20jobs%20and%20not%20enough%20people%20reviewing%20resum%C3%A9s.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20candidates%20should%20focus%20on%20finding%20ways%20to%20stand%20out%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20preparation%20starts%20before%20the%20job%20interview.%20Here%20are%20five%20things%20all%20candidates%20should%20do%20when%20they're%20preparing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Look%20for%20a%20job%20when%20you%20already%20have%20a%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20perspective%20is%20when%20someone%20thinks%2C%20%3Cem%3EI%20have%20a%20good%20job%20today%2C%20but%20I'm%20starting%20to%20feel%20interested%20in%20a%20new%20industry%3C%2Fem%3E.%20When%20that%20happens%2C%20I%20suggest%20reaching%20out%20to%20those%20in%20that%20field%2C%20connecting%20with%20them%2C%20and%20building%20relationships%20with%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20a%20software%20engineer%20is%20interested%20in%20a%20new%20B2B%20company%2C%20they%20should%20go%20out%20there%20and%20reach%20out%20to%20other%20engineers.%20They%20should%20take%20that%20connection%20to%20coffee%2C%20see%20what%20they're%20working%20on%2C%20and%20even%20offer%20them%20help.%20That%20way%2C%20when%20they%20do%20get%20an%20interview%2C%20they%20already%20have%20a%20warm%20connection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0You%20should%20always%20be%20poking%20your%20head%20over%20the%20fence%2C%20seeing%20what's%20out%20there%20and%20building%20relationships%20with%20others%20you'd%20like%20to%20work%20with.%20You%20should%20always%20be%20networking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20be%20bold%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20working%20at%20Doordash%20as%20the%20head%20of%20talent%2C%20we%20had%20someone%20interested%20in%20working%20for%20us.%20To%20make%20his%20interest%20known%2C%20he%20emailed%20the%20CEO%2021%20days%20in%20a%20row%2C%20a%20different%20email%20each%20time%2C%20in%20which%20he%20discussed%20why%20he%20wanted%20to%20work%20for%20Doordash%20and%20why%20we%20should%20interview%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20potentially%20risky%2C%20I%20personally%20thought%2C%20%3Cem%3EWe%20have%20to%20talk%20to%20this%20guy%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20always%20advise%20not%20to%20be%20too%20afraid%20of%20cold%20outreach%3A%20If%20you're%20really%20interested%20in%20a%20company%2C%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20those%20you%20want%20to%20work%20with%20%E2%80%94%20email%20the%20CEO%2C%20the%20head%20of%20talent%2C%20or%20the%20hiring%20manager%20and%20let%20them%20know%20why%20you're%20the%20right%20person%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Don't%20just%20prepare%20questions%3B%20go%20deeper%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20times%20people%20ask%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20the%20best%2010%20questions%20I%20can%20ask%20at%20the%20end%20of%20an%20interview%3F%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20not%20about%20preparing%20a%20list%20of%20questions%3B%20it's%20about%20more%20specific%20preparation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterviewees%20should%20be%20looking%20on%20the%20company's%20website%20and%20reading%20up%20on%20the%20company's%20values%2C%20vision%2C%20and%20mission%20statement%20to%20start.%20To%20take%20it%20a%20step%20further%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20founders%20these%20days%20are%20on%20a%20podcast%20or%20are%20online%20in%20some%20way.%20I%20think%20it's%20amazing%20when%20candidates%20can%20come%20in%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20listening%20to%20your%20founder%20say%20%5Bfill%20in%20the%20blank%5D%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20give%20specific%20examples%20of%20what%20they%20heard.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Be%20ready%20with%20stories%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20stories%20interviewees%20should%20consider%20when%20prepping%20for%20an%20interview.%20One%20should%20definitely%20be%20around%20a%20successful%20project%20they%20have%20completed%20and%20their%20role%20within%20that%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20is%20a%20career%20highlight%3A%20Candidates%20should%20tap%20into%20what%20they've%20done%20well.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20once%20interviewed%20a%20VP%20of%20HR%20who%20told%20me%20their%20career%20highlight%20was%20running%20a%20layoff.%C2%A0%20She%20mentioned%20how%20hard%20it%20was%20on%20her%20%E2%80%94%20she%20wasn't%20sleeping%20and%20felt%20very%20stressed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20an%20impacted%20employee%20came%20up%20and%20told%20her%20afterward%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20this%20must%20be%20hard%20on%20you.%20Thank%20you%20for%20treating%20me%20with%20respect.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20such%20a%20great%20story%20because%20it%20was%20counterintuitive%20and%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20candidates%20should%20be%20ready%20to%20share%20a%20lesson%20they've%20learned%20%E2%80%94%20a%20time%20you%20received%20difficult%2C%20constructive%20feedback%20that%20had%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20you.%20Explain%20how%20you%20processed%20it%2C%20and%20ultimately%20how%20it%20made%20you%20a%20better%20employee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20telling%20stories%20interviewees%20are%20able%20to%20show%20their%20deep%20inner%20fire%2C%20their%20motivation%2C%20and%20what%20drives%20them%20most.%20It%20also%20makes%20the%20interview%20more%20conversational%20and%20more%20engaging%20for%20both%20parties%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20never%20seen%20it%20backfire.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Find%20other%20ways%20to%20stand%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20when%20I%20was%20interviewing%20someone%20for%20a%20sales%20role%20at%20DoorDash%2C%20the%20candidate%20said%20they'd%20gone%20to%2010%20different%20restaurants%20that%20didn't%20offer%20the%20DoorDash%20service%20and%20asked%20them%2C%20why%20not%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20candidate%20then%20brought%20those%20answers%20to%20the%20interview%2C%20and%20also%20came%20prepared%20with%20solutions%20on%20how%20to%20get%20those%20restaurants%20on%20board.%20That%20candidate%20stood%20out%20to%20us%3B%20it%20was%20if%20they%20had%20done%20the%20job%20already%20before%20the%20interview.%20We%20ended%20up%20hiring%20them%20within%2024%20hours.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20feel%20like%20you're%20selling%20yourself%20in%20a%20super%20competitive%20world%2C%20that's%20what%20you%20have%20to%20do.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20you%20have%20to%20stand%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you're%20a%20recruiter%20with%20helpful%20tips%20to%20share%20and%20would%20like%20to%20tell%20your%20story%2C%20email%20Alyshia%20Hull%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aahull%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eahull%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20