%2C%20would%20need%20the%20support%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20lawmakers%20from%20this%20opposition%20bloc%20to%20have%20any%20hope%20of%20actually%20forming%20a%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20not%20been%20immediately%20clear%20after%20the%20vote%2C%20given%20PiS%E2%80%99%20apparently%20poor%20prospects%20trying%20to%20form%20a%20government%2C%20whether%20the%20ruling%20party%20would%20want%20Duda%20to%20nominate%20it%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20PiS%20leadership%C2%A0had%20used%20more%20vague%20language%20simply%20declaring%20itself%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwinner%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20election%20%E2%80%94%20as%20it%20had%20far%20more%20votes%20than%20any%20other%20single%20party%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwere-women-key-to-voting-out-polands-ruling-conservatives%2Fa-67214867%5C%22%3Elamenting%20its%20loss%20of%20control%20in%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20if%20Morawiecki%20can%E2%80%99t%20win%20the%20confidence%20vote%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20Morawiecki%20and%20PiS%20fail%2C%20it%20would%20then%20fall%20to%20lawmakers%20in%20parliament%20to%20pick%20a%20secondary%20candidate%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0quite%20probably%20Tusk.%20He%20would%20in%20turn%20then%20need%20to%20win%20a%20confidence%20vote%20in%20parliament%20to%20become%20prime%20minister%20and%20form%20a%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShould%20that%20stage%20fail%2C%20President%20Duda%20could%20either%20pick%20one%20last%20person%20to%20try%2C%20or%20call%20new%20elections%20if%20an%20intractable%20deadlock%20emerges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAddressing%20a%20rally%20shortly%20before%20Duda%20spoke%2C%20Tusk%20said%20that%20he%20would%20become%20prime%20minister%20in%20the%20end%2C%20whatever%20Duda%20decided%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20game%E2%80%A6%20unnecessarily%20exposes%20Polish%20interests%20to%20tangible%20losses%2C%20but%20I%20will%20tell%20you%20