osition%20members%2C%20including%20DMK%E2%80%99s%20Dayanidhi%20Maran%2C%20are%20said%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fstanding-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws-9016462%2F%5C%22%3Eopposed%20the%20usage%20of%20Hindi%20in%20the%20Bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20goes%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20constitution.%20However%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20not%20recommended%20a%20change%20of%20names%20or%20English%20versions%20of%20the%20names%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20members%20were%20also%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20bringing%20terror%2C%20corruption%20and%20organised%20crime%20under%20the%20new%20penal%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20recommendations%20made%20by%20members%20include%20having%20a%20comprehensive%20definition%20of%20community%20service%20and%20what%20it%20would%20entail%20as%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20%E2%80%93%20which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20%E2%80%93%20prescribes%20community%20service%20as%20an%20alternate%20form%20of%20punishment%20for%20some%20minor%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fparliament-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws%2Farticleshow%2F105007674.cms%5C%22%3Ethe%20committee%20has%20backed%20a%20gender-neutral%20adultery%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20punitive%20measures%20for%20non-consensual%20sex%20between%20men%2C%20women%20and%20transgender%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20proposed%20a%20reduction%20in%20sentence%20for%20those%20convicted%20of%20deterring%20public%20servants%20from%20discharging%20their%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20also%20recommended%20slashing%20the%20maximum%20prison%20term%20under%20Section%20353%20of%20the%20IPC%20from%20two%20years%20to%20one%20%E2%80%93%20citing%20that%20the%20law%20is%20often%20use