%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-59863859%5C%22%3Eimportant%20to%20his%20car%20company%2C%20Tesla%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20become%20obsessed%20by%20what%20he%20calls%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwoke-mind%20virus%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20he%20believes%20is%20infecting%20social%20discourse.%20Whatever%20the%20excesses%20and%20blind%20spots%20of%20those%20on%20the%20progressive%20side%20of%20politics%2C%20Musk%20sees%20this%20virus%20almost%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20longtime%20devotee%20of%20comics%20and%20science%20fiction%2C%20he%20has%20increasingly%20given%20rein%20to%20his%20conspiratorial%20tendencies%2C%20as%20if%20he%20really%20thinks%20The%20Matrix%20trilogy%20was%20a%20documentary%20series.%20In%20one%20of%20his%203am%20tweets%2C%20Musk%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CMy%20pronouns%20are%20Prosecute%2FFauci%E2%80%9D.%20As%20Isaacson%20trenchantly%20comments%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20made%20little%20sense%2C%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20funny%2C%20and%20managed%2C%20in%20just%20five%20words%2C%20to%20mock%3Cbr%3E%20transgender%20people%2C%20conjure%20up%20conspiracies%20about%20the%2081-year-old%20public%20health%3Cbr%3E%20official%20Anthony%20Fauci%2C%20scare%20off%20more%20advertisers%2C%20and%20create%20a%20new%20handful%20of%3Cbr%3E%20enemies%20who%20would%20now%20never%20buy%20Tesla.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3ENor%20does%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20belief%20in%20free%20speech%20extend%20to%20the%20social%20media%20postings%20of%20Twitter%20employees%20or%20their%20comments%20on%20internal%20Slack%20messaging.%20He%20trampled%20on%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20internal%20culture%20of%20healthy%20dissent%2C%20peremptorily%20firing%20three%20dozen%20employees%20who%20had%20criticised%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHis%20longstanding%2C%20largely%20successful%20mantra%20of%20getting%20things%20done%20cheaply%20and%20quickly%2C%20regardless%20of%20impediments%2C%20finally%20ran%20aground%20after%20he%20proposed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F02%2F26%2Ftechnology%2Ftwitter-layoffs.html%5C%22%3Ecutting%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20workforce%20by%2075%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20before%20Christmas%20last%20year%20he%20decided%20it%20was%20imperative%20to%20move%20all%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20servers%20from%20Sacramento%20to%20Oregon%20as%20a%20way%20of%20saving%20money.%20Remember%20how%20presidential%20aspirant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2023%2Fmay%2F24%2Fron-desantis-2024-twitter-launch-tech-outage%5C%22%3ERon%20De%20Santis%E2%80%99%20big%20live%20interview%20on%20X%20went%20horribly%20wrong%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%3F%20That%20was%20because%20of%20problems%20with%20the%20servers%2C%20writes%20Isaacson.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20the%20drastic%20cutting%20of%20the%20site%E2%80%99s%20moderators%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F10%2F09%2Fx-formerly-twitter-amplifies-disinformation-amid-the-israel-hamas-conflict.html%5C%22%3Efloods%20of%20misinformation%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20attack%20on%20Israel%20by%20Hamas%20on%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20also%20begun%20to%20realise%20that%20advertising%2C%20which%20previously%20comprised%2090%25%20of%20Twitter%E2%80%99s%20revenue%2C%20is%20susceptible%20to%20public%20perceptions.%20It%20fell%20by%20more%20than%20half%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20ownership%2C%20according%20to%20Isaacson.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGeopolitical%20implications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20Musk%20has%20found%20himself%20playing%20a%20key%20role%20in%20a%20war%20with%20geopolitical%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImmediately%20before%20invading%20Ukraine%20in%20early%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-behind-cyberattack-against-satellite-internet-modems-ukraine-eu-2022-05-10%2F%5C%22%3ERussia%20launched%20a%20malware%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20crippled%20the%20US%20satellite%20company%20providing%20internet%20service%20to%20Ukraine.%20Its%20deputy%20prime%20minister%2C%20Mykhailo%20Fedorov%2C%20reached%20out%20to%20Musk%20via%20Twitter%2C%20appealing%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMusk%20did%2C%20donating%20US%2480%20million%20worth%20of%20technology%20to%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20including%20Starlink%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fukraine-russia-war-spacex-starlink-satellite-internet%5C%22%3Esolar%20and%20battery%20kits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20were%20able%20to%20defeat%20Russian%20efforts%20to%20jam%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMusk%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20was%20widely%20praised%2C%20but%20in%20September%202022%2C%20when%20the%20Ukrainians%20planned%20to%20use%20Starlink%20to%20guide%20a%20drone%20attack%20on%20the%20Russian%20naval%20fleet%20at%20Sevastopol%20in%20Crimea%2C%20he%20refused%20to%20help.%20He%20had%20been%20listening%20to%20the%20Russian%20ambassador%2C%20who%20had%20reached%20out%20to%20him%20a%20few%20weeks%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERussia%20had%20annexed%20Crimea%20in%202014%20and%20the%20ambassador%20persuaded%20him%20not%20only%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20inalienable%20right%20to%20Crimea%2C%20but%20of%20the%20prospect%20of%20nuclear%20war%20if%20the%20Ukrainians%20were%20allowed%20to%20try%20and%20retake%20it.%20He%20told%20Isaacson%20he%20had%20been%20studying%20foreign%20policy%20and%20military%20history%3A%20%E2%80%9CMusk%20explained%20to%20me%20the%20details%20of%20Russian%20law%20and%20doctrine%20that%20decreed%20such%20a%20response.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHas%20technology%20put%20an%20individual%20private%20citizen%20in%20such%20a%20position%20before%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndividual%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Krupp%20manufacturing%20company%2C%20notoriously%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20arming%20Nazi%20Germany.%20Individual%20media%20proprietors%2C%20such