ompared%20with%20traditional%20buildings%2C%20increasing%20energy%20efficiency%20and%20decreasing%20carbon%20emissions.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20low-carbon%20materials%20in%20green%20buildings%20reduce%20lifecycle%20emissions%20of%20buildings%20by%20up%20to%2030%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20conserve%20energy%20in%20their%20unique%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F244161%2Fthese-10-eco-friendly-homes-will-inspire-you-to-live-sustainably%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esustainable%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20father-son%20pair%20have%20employed%20an%20innovative%20masonry%20technique%2C%C2%A0the%20%E2%80%98Rat%20Trap%20Bond%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20was%20popularised%20by%20renowned%20architect%20Laurie%20Baker%20for%20passive%20cooling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20traditional%20methods%2C%20this%20technique%20involves%20placing%20the%20bricks%20vertically%20rather%20than%20horizontally%2C%20aiding%20in%20temperature%20regulation%20and%20energy%20conservation%20within%20the%20structure.%20It%20creates%20a%20cavity%20in%20the%20walls%20and%20allows%20the%20thickness%20to%20remain%20the%20same%20as%20a%20conventional%20brick%20masonry%20wall.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20cavity%20helps%20cut%20down%20the%20number%20of%20bricks%20and%20mortar%20used%20by%20up%20to%2030%20percent.%20This%20further%20reduces%20carbon%20footprints%20and%20costs%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ramachandrudu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Fsustainable-home-4-1698759671.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20container%20house%20boasts%20two%20bedrooms%2C%20a%20drawing%20room%2C%20two%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20a%20staircase.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F